continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20currently%20employs%20about%201.5%20million%20workers%2C%20according%20to%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsustainability.aboutamazon.com%2Femployees%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewebsite%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20is%20unclear%20how%20many%20employees%2C%20or%20in%20which%20sectors%2C%20would%20be%20affected%20by%20AI-driven%20job%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20previously%20reported%20that%20the%20company%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-freezes-hiring-budget-retail-business-this-year-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efreezing%20its%20hiring%20budget%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20its%20retail%20business%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20March%20earnings%20call%2C%20the%20company%20announced%20it%20would%20spend%20%24100%20billion%20on%20capital%20expenditures%2C%20mostly%20driven%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-earnings-call-report-amzn-stock-live-updates-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20investments%20and%20data%20centers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Business%20Insider%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJassy%20is%20not%20the%20first%20executive%20to%20suggest%20that%20advancements%20in%20AI%20will%20likely%20translate%20to%20job%20cuts%20in%20their%20businesses.%20The%20conversations%20around%20these%20types%20of%20reductions%20in%20force%20have%20become%20increasingly%20common%20%E2%80%94%20and%20less%20hypothetical.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllison%20Kirkby%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20British%20telecom%20giant%20BT%2C%20warned%20that%20AI%20may%20lead%20to%20further%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceo-bt-telecoms-giant-warns-more-ai-driven-job-cuts-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejob%20cuts%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20firm%20after%20BT%20in%202023%20announced%20plans%20to%20eliminate%20as%20many%20as%2055%2C000%20roles%20by%202030%2C%20Business%20Insider%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20late%20May%2C%20An